        </mj-text> 
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-feb-4-1.png" alt="Trump delays tariff on Canada for 30-days" href="https://www.longandshort.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">Donald Trump and Justin Trudeau at the recent G7 Summit in Quebec. Credits: Evan Vucci/AP
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Prime Minister Justin Trudeau reached a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-04-02-2025-h1-1-last-minute-agreement" target="_blank">last-minute agreement</a> with Donald Trump to secure a 30-day reprieve from US tariffs. Canada has agreed to increase border security efforts and has announced new measures targeting the cross-border trade of fentanyl. The country will deploy around 10,000 border personnel, tighten visa rules, and invest $138 million in intelligence operations.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The agreement has de-escalated the growing tensions that have been casting shadows over the global financial markets in recent weeks. Trump’s proposed 25% tariffs sparked several sectors' concerns about supply chain disruptions. The Canadian dollar had taken heavy blows, trading at <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-04-02-2025-h1-2-record-low" target="_blank">a record low</a> against the greenback. With a 30-day deadline in sight, Canadian officials are expected to intensify efforts to ensure the proposed tariffs don’t go into effect next month.</p>
        </mj-text>
