            <strong>🇸🇦 Riyadh Air eyes 50 widebody jets as it pushes Saudi aviation ambitions</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Riyadh Air is in discussions with Boeing and Airbus regarding an order of up to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-04-02-2025-wn1-5-50-additional-widebody-aircraft" target="_blank">50 additional widebody aircraft</a>. The airline is conceding the purchase of Airbus A350-1000 and Boeing 777X. However, both of these aircraft present unique challenges. Boeing’s 777X is still awaiting certification, while the A350-1000 faces performance concerns in extreme climates.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Saudi Arabia has aggressively expanded its aviation sector as part of its Vision 2030 strategy. The country plans to diversify its economy away from oil and establish itself as a global tourism hub. Riyadh Air is backed by Saudi Arabia’s Public Investment Fund (PIF).
