            <strong>🇫🇷 L’Oreal offloads €3 billion of Sanofi stock</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          L’Oreal SA is selling a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-04-02-2025-wn2-3-billion-stake" target="_blank">$3.09 billion stake</a> in Sanofi back to the company as part of a strategic move to optimize its balance sheet. The cosmetic giant is offloading 29.6 million shares at $104.50 each, reducing its ownership in Sanofi from 9.4% to 7.2%.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Sanofi's repurchase of its stock is part of its previously announced share buyback program. The company’s shares have soared over the past year, gaining around 20%, whereas L’Oreal stock has struggled due to weak demand in China. L’Oreal has been acquisitive recently, notably buying soap maker Aesop in a transaction worth $2.6 billion in 2023.
        </p>
