            <strong>🇦🇹 Bankrupt Signa seeks €370M from Vienna Park Hyatt sale</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The bankrupt Austrian real estate giant Signa Prime Selection AG is <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-04-02-2025-wn3-7-preparing-to-sell" target="_blank">preparing to sell</a> the Vienna Park Hyatt hotel and adjoining properties. The sale is expected to generate around $361 million for the firm. In a 2022 presentation to investors seen by Bloomberg, Signa valued the building at $434 million.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          The sale comes amidst Signa’s efforts to liquidate assets to repay creditors after the collapse of its property empire. Signa Holding <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-04-01-2025-wn3-8-filed-for-insolvency" target="_blank">filed for insolvency</a> in November 2023. The company aggressively expanded into high-end real estate across Europe, relying on billions in borrowed funds. As interest rates increased, the firm could not meet debt obligations and became insolvent.
          </p>
