              margin-top: 2px !important;">What are Gray Rhino events?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.longandshort.com/email/images/ls-feb-4-3.png" alt="What are Gray Rhino Events?" href="https://www.longandshort.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;">
            Two men carrying the Lehman Brothers sign board. Credits: Classunity.org
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000"> 
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"><a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-04-02-2025-f1-17-gray-rhino" target="_blank">Gray Rhino</a> events refer to <strong>highly probable</strong> and consequential risks that are <strong>overlooked</strong> despite clear <strong>warning signs</strong>. Unlike black swan events, Gray Rhino events are not unpredictable and can be forecasted.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          Several factors contribute to why people ignore these seemingly obvious warning signs. <strong>Cognitive biases, such as optimism and status quo bias</strong>, often lead decision-makers to underestimate risks or delay action.
         </p>
         <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Example: 2008 financial crisis</strong>
         </p>
         <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">A classic example of a gray rhino event is the 2008 financial crisis. Several warning signs included excessive risk-taking, unsustainable debt, and lax regulations, yet stakeholders failed to address the problems that led to the crisis.
         </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
